    "statement": "<p>A sequence <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">0</sub>,\u2009<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>,\u2009...,\u2009<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>t</i>\u2009-\u20091</sub></span> is called increasing if <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>i</i>\u2009-\u20091</sub>\u2009&lt;\u2009<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>i</i></sub></span> for each <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>i</i>:\u20090\u2009&lt;\u2009<i>i</i>\u2009&lt;\u2009<i>t</i></span>.</p><p>You are given a sequence <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>b</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">0</sub>,\u2009<i>b</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>,\u2009...,\u2009<i>b</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>n</i>\u2009-\u20091</sub></span> and a positive integer <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>d</i></span>. In each move you may choose one element of the given sequence and add <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>d</i></span> to it. What is the least number of moves required to make the given sequence increasing?</p>",
